If step 4 fails or streaming replication is not configured, or if the connection is later disconnected,
the standby goes back to step 2 and tries to restore the file from the archive again.
This loop of retries from the archive, pg_wal, and via streaming replication goes on until
the server is stopped or failover is triggered by a trigger file.
